Package cafe.models

Class StoreOrders

  • java.lang.Object
    • cafe.models.StoreOrders
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Customizable
    public class StoreOrders
extends java.lang.Object
implements Customizable
    All the orders for the store. This class follows the singleton design pattern as we really want one shared instance to be shared across the project from multiple controllers as easy as possible. This abstraction proves to be very effective in our particular case.
    Author:
    Reagan McFarland, Vatche Kafafian

      • resetOrderIds

        public void resetOrderIds()
        Reset the order Ids of the orders. We need this because when you delete an order, the Ids are no longer mapped to the index correctly, and you end up with ID gaps that don't make much sense for the user.
